"""Bundled Rare-item WeightedSum archetype rules.

Ported verbatim (not re-derived) from a real, working Exiled Bot 2 pickit
file the owner supplied ("Barbintha - Fate Of The Vaal - Generated Pickit
V0.1.ipd"), covering Amulets/Belts/Body Armour/Boots/Gloves/Helmets/Rings/
Quivers/Sceptres/Shields/Spears/Wands/Staves/Jewels/Quarterstaves. Kept as
literal bundled text rather than re-generated from formulas: every stat id
and WeightedSum weight here is exactly what the owner's own working pickit
uses, so re-typing it risks a transcription error nobody would notice until
it silently mismatched in-game. A single tab-wide toggle gates whether this
section is emitted -- no per-class granularity yet.

Claws/Daggers/Flails were removed from the source file -- explicitly excluded
elsewhere in this project (see CRAFT_BASE class-group comments) and the owner
confirmed they should not be included here either.

Multi-line archetype banners ("BOOTS" / "ARMOUR + ES" as two separate title
lines) were merged into one combined title line ("BOOTS - ARMOUR + ES") --
the Preview tab's section parser only ever captures a single line as a
section title, so the un-merged two-line form caused it to split one
archetype into a mislabeled fragment (e.g. seven separate "BOOTS" entries
in the sidebar, each showing only a slice of the real rule count).
"""

def build_rare_archetype_rules(enabled: bool) -> list:
    """Rare Archetypes section: on/off only (see module docstring). Returns
    [] when disabled so it costs nothing in the output."""
    if not enabled:
        return []
    from exilebot_pickit.generator import header_major as _header_major  # avoid circular import
    return [
        _header_major("Rare Archetypes"),
        "",
        "//  Per-build WeightedSum rules bundled from a real working pickit.                //",
        "//  Toggle this section in Settings.                                               //",
        "",
    ] + RARE_ARCHETYPE_LINES


